snippet: Dozens of people were injured in a renewed outburst of protest and violence, as Egypt enters what may be a climactic stage of its turbulent shift from military rule.
abstract: Deadly clashes erupt again in Egypt, in a sign of growing tensions as the country nears end of turbulent 15-month political transition from military rule; fighting starts after protesters defy warning by the ruling military council not to approach the ministry building.

byline.original: By KAREEM FAHIM and LIAM STACK
